www.devkyfb.com site — so my request never reaches the API at all. The Route 53 CNAME itself is correct: resolving through public DNS (8.8.8.8) 
returns the right API Gateway target (d-txqyeb3zoc.execute-api... / 54.225.164.69), while only our internal resolver returns CloudFront 
— so this is purely a testing artifact from inside the corporate network, not an API problem. Production clients connect over the open internet 
using public DNS, so they get the correct API Gateway address and never touch the CloudFront path; on top of that, traffic is gated by both mTLS 
(a request with no client cert is rejected before reaching the Lambda — confirmed when I forced the request to the correct IP) and 
the API Gateway IP allowlist, so only whitelisted clients presenting a valid certificate get through. To remove all doubt, 
the actual client can run nslookup realtimeinsurance-soap-api-dev.devkyfb.com from their own network and confirm they get the API Gateway 
address rather than CloudFront — and separately, the internal-DNS-to-CloudFront quirk is worth flagging to whoever owns the devkyfb.com zone, 
